</h2>
<h3>
    Seasonal Migration Patterns
</h3>
<p>
    Sockeye salmon usually start migrating from the Pacific Ocean to Oregon’s inland waters in late spring, peaking between June and early August. Their presence in the Willamette River system—accessible from Salem—aligns with warmer weather and increased angling activity.
</p>
