<h3>
    Ideal Temperature for Sockeye
</h3>
<p>
    Sockeye salmon thrive in water temperatures between <strong>50°F and 58°F (10°C to 14°C)</strong>. When temperatures rise above this range in late summer, the fish often move to deeper, cooler pools or upstream tributaries with shaded areas.
</p>
<h3>
    Impact of Water Clarity and Flow Rates
</h3>
<p>
    Water clarity plays a major role in visibility and presentation. After rainfall, rivers may become murky, reducing sockeye activity. Moderate flow rates are ideal; if the current is too strong, sockeye may avoid moving upstream altogether or rest in slower pockets along the banks.
</p>
